#assumotions check
# model_randomis<-lmer(stresslevel ~ week + (1+week|subject),data=stress.long)
par (mfrow= c(1,2))
# Random Intercept
qqnorm(ranef(model_randomis)$subject[["(Intercept)"]],main="Random Intercept")
qqline(ranef(model_randomis)$subject[["(Intercept)"]])
# Random Slope
qqnorm(ranef(model_randomis)$subject[["variable"]],main="Random Slope")
qqline(ranef(model_randomis)$subject[["variable"]])

#Residuals
par(mfrow=c(1,1))
Residuals<-residuals(model_randomis)
qqnorm(Residuals,main="Residuals")
qqline(Residuals)

#constant variance
plot(model_randomis,main="Constant Variance Assumption")

The independent, constant var and normal residuals all fit. So assumptions checked well.

so we choose m3 as new model.

Then compare m3 and m0.

For m0 we have smaller AIC,BIC and smaller p-value, so compared m0 and m3, we choose m0.

The final model we choose is m0: lmer(choles~ treatment + month + (1|id), data = choles.long).

The independent, constant var and normal residuals all fit. So assumptions checked well.
